\fs42 \cf2 Italian Polenta Cakes
\fs56 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl280\ql\qnatural

\b0\fs38 \cf2 \

\fs44 1 cup instant polenta\
2 cups of chicken broth\
1 cup milk\
1/2 cup half-and-half\
2 teaspoons of italian seasoning\
1/4 cup parmesan cheese\
1 teaspoon lemon zest\
salt and pepper to taste\
olive oil\
butter\
\
Bring chicken broth, milk, half-and-half, and italian seasoning to a boil in a sauce pan together. Remove from heat and add polenta stirring until thick and all the liquid is absorbed. \'a0Add parmesan, lemon zest, and salt and pepper and pour into 9" x 6" pan.* \'a0Allow to cool at room temperature for thirty minutes before covering and cooling completely in the fridge.* \'a0When ready to serve, cut into squares and saut\'e9 on both sides in pan with olive oil and butter until lightly browned.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl280\ql\qnatural

\i\fs38 \cf2 Cook's Note: A 8" x 8" or 9" x 9" pan will work as well, the thickness of the polenta cakes will just change. \'a0
\i0\fs44 \

\i\fs38 The polenta will keep in the fridge for a few days before saut\'e9ed. \'a0
